he efficacy of pazopanib, a potent and selective multi-targeted  of 1, 2, 3, platelet-derived growth factor receptor-±/², and c-kit, in  patients has been evaluated in several trials. s monotherapy, pazopanib was demonstrated to be active in treatment-naive patients with tage / resectable .64 n 2012, the combination of pazopanib and erlotinib was evaluated in a hase b study, demonstrating a manageable toxicity profile.64 urrently, another hase  trial (01027598) is ongoing to test erlotinib/pazopanib or erlotinib/placebo in pretreated  patients. he results of a hase b trial (00619424) evaluating pazopanib in combination with either erlotinib or pemetrexed in  patients are still to come. t this time, pazopanib is being studied in combination with vinorelbine (01060514) or paclitaxel (00866528 and 01179269), in  third-line setting (01049776), in comparison with pemetrexed as maintenance therapy in tage  nonsquamous  (01313663), as second-line therapy after first-line chemotherapy (01208064) or treatments containing bevacizumab (01262820), and as adjuvant therapy (00775307).
